obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (4569)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287&sectionId=4569&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may he called The Forward Contracts`
  line `(Regulation) Act, 1952^1.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India; ^2***`
  line
  line `(3) Chapter I shall come into force at once, and the remaining provisions shall come into force on`
  line `such date^3`
  line `or dates as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint, and`
  line `different dates may he appointed for different provisions of this Act, for different States or areas, and for`
  line `different goods or classes of good.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. This Act has been extended to:--`
  line
  line `(i) Pondicherry (with modification), vide notification No. S.O. 3865, dated 29-12-1962, see Gazette of India, Part II,`
  line `sec. 3(ii).`
  line
  line `(ii) Dadra and Nagar Haveli by Reg. 6 of 1963, s. 2 and First Schedule: and`
  line
  line `(iii) Goa, Daman and Diu (with modification), vide notification No. G.S.R. 962, dated 24-6-1967, see Gazette of India, Part II,`
  line `sec. 3(i).`
  line
  line `2. The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 62 of 1960, s. 2 (w.e.f. 28-12-1960).`
  line
  line `3. Chapters II and VI were brought into force in the whole of India except the State of Jammu and Kashmir on the 24th August,`
  line `1953, vide notification No. S. R.O. 1618, dated the 24th August, 1953; see Gazette of India, Part II, sec. 3.`
  line `Provisions of this Act except Chapter I came into force in the State of Jammu and Kashmir on the 22nd September, 1962,`
  line `vide notification No. S.O. 2895, dated the 15th September, 1962, see Gazette of India, Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (4570)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287&sectionId=4570&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "association" means any body of individuals, whether incorporated or not, constituted for the`
  line `purpose of regulating and controlling the business of the sale or purchase of any goods;`
  line
  line `(b) "Commission" means the Forward Markets Commission established under section 3;`
  line
  line `(c) "forward contract" means a contract for the delivery of goods ^1*** and which is not a ready`
  line `delivery contract;`
  line
  line `(d) "goods" means every kind of movable property other than actionable claims, money and`
  line securities;
  line
  line `(e) "Government security" means a Government security as defined in the Public Debt Act, 1944`
  line `(18 of 1944);`
  line
  line `(f) "non-transferable specific delivery contract" means a specific delivery contract, the rights or`
  line `liabilities under which or under any delivery order, railway receipt, bill of lading, warehouse receipt`
  line `or any other document of title relating thereto are not transferable;`
  line
  line `(g) "option in goods" means an agreement, by whatever name called, for the purchase or sale of a`
  line `right to buy or sell, or a right to buy and sell, goods in future, and includes a teji, a mandi, a`
  line `teji-mandi, a galli, a put, a call or a put and call in goods;`
  line
  line `(h) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(i) "ready delivery contract" means a contract which provides for the delivery of goods and the`
  line `payment of a price therefor, either immediately or within such period not exceeding eleven days after the date of the contract and subject to such conditions as the Central Government may, by notification`
  line `in the Official Gazette, specify in respect of any goods, the period under such contract not being`
  line `capable of extension by the mutual consent of the parties thereto or otherwise;`
  line
  line `^2[Provided that where any such contract is performed either wholly, or in part,--`
  line
  line `(1) by tendering of the documents of title to the goods covered by the contract by any party thereto`
  line `(not being a commission agent or a bank) who has acquired ownership of the said documents by purchase,`
  line `exchange or otherwise, to any other person (including a commission agent but not including a bank); or`
  line
  line `(2) by the realisation of any sum of money, being the difference between the contract rate and the`
  line `settlement rate or clearing rate or the rate of any offsetting contract; or`
  line
  line `(3) by any other means whatsoever,`
  line
  line `and as a result of which the actual tendering of the goods covered by the contract or the payment of the`
  line `full price therefor is dispensed with, then, such contract shall not be deemed to be a ready delivery`
  line contract.
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purpose of this clause,--`
  line
  line `(i) "bank" includes any banking company as defined in the Banking Regulation Act, 1949`
  line `(10 of 1949), a co-operative bank as defined in the Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934), the`
  line `Slate Bank of India and any of its subsidiaries and any corresponding new bank constituted under`
  line `section 3 of the Banking Companies (Acquisition and Transfer of Undertakings) Act, 1970`
  line `(5 of 1970);`
  line
  line `(ii) "commission agent" means a person who, in the ordinary course of business, makes contract`
  line `for the sale or purchase of goods for others for a remuneration (whether known as commission or`
  line `otherwise) which is determined in the contract itself or determinate from the terms of the contract, in`
  line `either case, only with reference to the quantity of goods or to the price therefor as stipulated in the`
  line contract.]
  line
  line `^3[(j) "recognised association" means an association to which recognition for the time being has`
  line `been granted by the Central Government under section 6 in respect of goods or classes of goods`
  line `specified in such recognition;`
  line
  line `(jj) "registered association" means an association to which for the time being a certificate of`
  line `registration has been granted by the Commission under section 14B;]`
  line
  line `(k) "rules", with reference to the rules relating in general to the constitution and management of`
  line `an association, includes in the case of an incorporated association its memorandum and articles of`
  line association;
  line
  line `(l) "securities" includes shares, scrips, stocks, bonds, debentures, debenture-stocks or other`
  line `marketable securities of a like nature in or of any incorporated company or other body corporate and`
  line `also Government securities;`
  line
  line `(m) "specific delivery contract" means a forward contract which provides for the actual delivery`
  line `of specific qualities or types of goods during a specified future period at a price fixed thereby or to be`
  line `fixed in the manner thereby agreed and in which the names of both the buyer and the seller are`
  line mentioned;
  line
  line `(n) "transferable specific delivery contract" means a specific delivery contract which is not a`
  line `non-transferable specific delivery contract, ^4[and which is subject to such conditions relating to its`
  line `transferability as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify in this`
  line behalf.]
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "at a future date" omitted by Act 53 of 1971, s. 2 (w.e.f. 11-10-1971).`
  line
  line `2. Added by Act 53 of 1971, s. 2 (w.e.f. 11-10-1971).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 62 of 1960, s. 3, for Clause (j) (w.e.f. 28-12-1960).`
  line
  line `4. Added by s. 3, ibid. (w.e.f. 28-12-1960).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (4571)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Establishment and constitution of the Forward Markets Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287&sectionId=4571&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central`
  line `Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette establish a Commission to be called the Forward`
  line `Markets Commission for the purpose of exercising such functions and discharging such duties as may be`
  line `assigned to the Commission by or under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commission shall consist of not less than two, ^1[but not exceeding four], members appointed`
  line `by the Central Government ^2[one of them being nominated by the Central Government to be the`
  line `Chairman thereof; and the Chairman and the other member or members shall be either whole-time or`
  line `part-time as the Central Government may direct]:`
  line
  line `^3[Provided that the members to be so appointed shall be persons of ability, integrity and standing who`
  line `have shown capacity in dealing with problems relating to commerce or commodity markets, or in`
  line `administration or who have special knowledge or practical experience in any matter which renders them`
  line `suitable for appointment on the Commission.]`
  line
  line `(3) No person shall be qualified for appointment as, or for continuing to be, a member of the`
  line `Commission if he has, directly or indirectly, any such financial or other interest as is likely to affect`
  line `prejudicially his functions as a member of the Commission, and every member shall, whenever required`
  line `by the Central Government so to do, furnish to it such information as it may require for the purpose of`
  line `securing compliance with the provisions of this sub-section.`
  line
  line `(4) No member of the Commission shall hold office for a period of more than three years from the`
  line `date of his appointment, and a member relinquishing his office on the expiry of his term shall be eligible`
  line `for reappointment.`
  line
  line `(5) The other terms and conditions of service of members of the Commission shall be such as may be`
  line prescribed.
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 62 of 1960, s. 4, for "but not exceeding three" (w.e.f. 28-12-1960).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 46 of 1953, s. 2, for certain words (w.e.f. 23-12-1953).`
  line
  line `3. The proviso subs. by Act 62 of 1960, s. 4 (w.e.f. 28-12-1960).`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (4572)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Functions of the Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287&sectionId=4572&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `The functions of the Commission shall be--`
  line
  line `(a) to advise the Central Government in respect of the recognition of, or the withdrawal of`
  line `recognition from, any association or in respect of any other matter arising out of the administration of`
  line `this Act;`
  line
  line `^1[(b) to keep forward markets under observation and to take such action in relation to them as it`
  line `may consider necessary, in exercise of the powers assigned to it by or under this Act;]`
  line
  line `(c) to collect and whenever the Commission thinks it necessary publish information regarding the`
  line `trading conditions in respect of goods to which any of the provisions of this Act is made applicable,`
  line `including information regarding supply, demand and prices, and to submit to the Central Government`
  line `periodical reports on the operation of this Act and on the working of forward markets relating to such`
  line goods;
  line
  line `(d) to make recommendations generally with a view to improving the organisation and working`
  line `of forward markets;`
  line
  line `(e) to undertake the inspection of the accounts and other documents of ^2[any recognised`
  line `association or registered association or any member of such association] whenever it considers it`
  line `necessary; and`
  line
  line `(f) to perform such other duties and exercise such other powers as may be assigned to the`
  line `Commission by or under this Act, or as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 5, ibid., for clause (b) (w.e.f. 28-12-1960).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 5, ibid., for "any recognised association" (w.e.f. 28-12-1960).`
obj_root_law_sections_4_a:
  sectionId (4573)
  sectionNo 4A
  orderNo 5
  title `Powers of the Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 62 of 1960, s. 6 (w.e.f. 28-12-1960).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287&sectionId=4573&sectionno=4A&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287
obj_root_law_sections_4_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[4A. Powers of the Commission.--(1) The Commission shall in the performance of its functions,`
  line `have all the powers of a civil court under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), while trying a`
  line `suit in respect of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) summoning and enforcing the attendance of any person and examining him on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) requiring the discovery and production of any document;`
  line
  line `(c) receiving evidence on affidavits;`
  line
  line `(d) requisitioning any public record or copy thereof from any office;`
  line
  line `(e) any matter which may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commission shall have the power to require any person, subject to any privilege which may`
  line `be claimed by that person under any law for the time being in force, to furnish information on such points`
  line `or matters as, in the opinion of the Commission, may be useful for, or relevant to, any matter under the`
  line `consideration of the Commission and any person so required shall be deemed to be legally bound to`
  line `furnish such information within the meaning of section 176 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
  line
  line `(3) The Commission shall be deemed to be a Civil Court and when any offence described in`
  line `section 175, section 178, section 179, section 180 or section 228 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860) is`
  line `committed in the view or presence of the Commission, the Commission may, after recording the facts`
  line `constituting the offence and the statement of the accused as provided for in the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1898 (5 of 1898), forward the case to a magistrate having jurisdiction to try the same and the`
  line `magistrate to whom any such case is forwarded shall proceed to hear the complaint against the accused as`
  line `if the case has been forwarded to him under section 482 of the said Code.`
  line
  line `(4) Any proceeding before the Commission shall be deemed to be a judicial proceeding within the`
  line `meaning of sections 193 and 228 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of enforcing attendance of witnesses, the local limits of the`
  line `Commission's jurisdiction shall be the limits of the territory of India.]`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (4574)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 6
  title `Application for recognition of associations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287&sectionId=4574&sectionno=5&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any association concerned with the regulation`
  line `and control of forward contracts which is desirous of being recognised for the purposes of this Act may`
  line `make an application in the prescribed manner to the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) Every application made under sub-section (1) shall contain such particulars as may be prescribed`
  line `and shall be accompanied by a copy of the bye-laws for the regulation and control of forward contracts`
  line `and also a copy of the rules relating in general to the constitution of the association, and in particular, to--`
  line
  line `(a) the governing body of such association, its constitution and powers of management and the`
  line `manner in which its business is to be transacted;`
  line
  line `(b) the powers and duties of the office-bearers of the association;`
  line
  line `(c) the admission into the association of various classes of members, the qualifications of`
  line `members, and the exclusion, suspension, expulsion and readmission of members therefrom or there`
  line into;
  line
  line `(d) the procedure for registration of partnerships as members of the association and the`
  line `nomination and appointment of authorised representatives and clerks.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (4575)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 7
  title `Grant of recognition to association.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287&sectionId=4575&sectionno=6&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the Central Government, after making such inquiry as`
  line `may be necessary in this behalf and after obtaining such further information, if any, as it may require, is`
  line `satisfied that it would be in the interest of the trade and also in the public interest to grant recognition to`
  line `the association which has made an application under section 5, it may grant recognition to the association in such form and subject to such conditions as may be prescribed or specified, and shall specify in such`
  line `recognition the goods or classes of goods with respect to which forward contracts may be entered into`
  line `between members of such association or through or with any such member.`
  line
  line `(2) Before granting recognition under sub-section (1), the Central Government may, by order`
  line direct,--
  line
  line `(a) that there shall be no limitation on the number of members of the association or that there`
  line `shall be such limitation on the number of members as may be specified;`
  line
  line `(b) that the association shall provide for the appointment by the Central Government of a person,`
  line `whether a member of the association or not, as its representative on, and of not more than three`
  line `persons representing interests not directly represented through membership of the association as`
  line `member or members of, the governing body of such association, and may require the association to`
  line `incorporate in its rules any such direction and the conditions, if any, accompanying it.`
  line
  line `(3) No rules of a recognised association shall be amended except with the approval of the Central`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(4) Every grant of recognition under this section shall be published in the Gazette of India and also in`
  line `the Official Gazette of the State in which the principal office of the recognised association is situate, and`
  line `such recognition shall have effect as from the date of its publication in the Gazette of India.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (4576)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 8
  title `Withdrawal of recognition.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287&sectionId=4576&sectionno=7&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `If the Central Government is of opinion that any recognition`
  line `granted to an association under the provisions of this Act should, in the interest of the trade or in the`
  line `public interest, be withdrawn, the Central Government may, after giving a reasonable opportunity to the`
  line `association to be heard in the matter withdraw, by notification in the Official Gazette, the recognition`
  line `granted to the said association:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such withdrawal shall affect the validity of any contract entered into or made before`
  line `the date of the notification, and the Central Government may make such provision as it deems fit in the`
  line `notification of withdrawal or in any subsequent notification similarly published for the due performance`
  line `of any contracts outstanding on that date.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (4577)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 9
  title `Power of Central Government to call for periodical returns or direct inquiries to be made.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287&sectionId=4577&sectionno=8&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) Every recognised association and every member thereof shall furnish to the Central`
  line `Government such periodical returns relating to its affairs, or the affairs of its members, as the case may`
  line `be, as may be prescribed.]`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the provisions contained in sub-section (1), where the Central Government`
  line `considers it expedient so to do, it may, by order in writing,--`
  line
  line `(a) call upon a recognised association ^2[or a member thereof] to furnish in writing such`
  line `information or explanation relating to its affairs or the affairs of any of its members ^2[or his affairs, as`
  line `the case may be] as the Central Government may require, or`
  line
  line `(b) appoint one or more persons to make an inquiry in relation to the affairs of such association or`
  line `the affairs of any of its members and submit a report of the result of such inquiry to the Central`
  line `Government within such time as may be specified in the order or, in the alternative, direct the inquiry`
  line `to be made, and the report to be submitted, by the governing body of such association acting jointly`
  line `with one or more representatives of the Central Government; and`
  line
  line `(c) direct the Commission to inspect the accounts and other documents of any recognised`
  line `association or of any of its members and submit its report thereon to the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) Where an inquiry in relation to the affairs of a recognised association or the affairs of any of its`
  line `members has been undertaken under sub-section (2)--`
  line
  line `(a) every director, manager, secretary or other officer of such association,`
  line
  line `(b) every member of such association,`
  line
  line `(c) if the member of the association is a firm, every partner, manager, secretary or other officer of`
  line `the firm, and`
  line
  line `(d) every other person or body of persons who had dealings in the course of business with any of`
  line `the persons mentioned in clauses (a), (b) and (c),`
  line
  line `shall be bound to produce before the authority making the inquiry, all such books, accounts,`
  line `correspondence and other documents in his custody or power relating to, or having a bearing on the`
  line `subject-matter of, such inquiry and also to furnish the authority with any such statement or information`
  line `relating thereto as may be required of him, within such time as may be specified.`
  line
  line `^3[(4) Every recognised association and every member thereof shall maintain such books of account`
  line `and other documents as the Commission may specify and the books of account and other documents so`
  line `specified shall be preserved for such period not exceeding three years as the Commission may specify and`
  line `shall be subject to inspection at all reasonable times by the Commission.]`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 62 of 1960, s. 7, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 28-12-1960).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 7, ibid. (w.e.f. 28-12-1960).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 62 of 1960, s. 7 (w.e.f. 28-12-1960).`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (4578)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 10
  title `Furnishing of annual reports to the Central Government by recognised associations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 8, ibid., for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 28-12-1960).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287&sectionId=4578&sectionno=9&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)`
  line `Every recognised association shall furnish to the Commission three copies of its annual report.]`
  line
  line `(2) Such annual report shall contain such particulars as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_a:
  sectionId (4579)
  sectionNo 9A
  orderNo 11
  title `Power of recognised association to make rules respecting grouping of members, restricting voting rights, etc., in special cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287&sectionId=4579&sectionno=9A&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287
obj_root_law_sections_9_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[9A. Power of recognised association to make rules respecting grouping of members,`
  line `restricting voting rights, etc., in special cases.--(1) A recognised association may make rules or amend`
  line `any rules made by it to provide for all or any of the following matters namely,--`
  line
  line `^2[(a) the admission of a firm or a Hindu undivided family as a member,]`
  line
  line `^3[(b)] the grouping of the members of the association according to functional or local interests,`
  line `the reservation of seats on its governing body for members belonging to each group and appointment`
  line `of members to such reserved seats--`
  line
  line `(i) by election exclusively by the members of the association from among persons chosen by`
  line `the members belonging to the group concerned;`
  line
  line `(ii) by election by all the members of the association;`
  line
  line `(iii) by election by all the members belonging to the group concerned for the purpose;`
  line
  line `^3[(c)] the restriction of voting rights in respect of any matter placed before the association at any`
  line `meeting to those members only who, by reason of their functional or local interests, are actually`
  line `interested in such matter,`
  line
  line `^3[(d)] the regulation of voting rights in respect of any matter placed before the association at any`
  line `meeting so that each member may be entitled to have one vote only, irrespective of his share of the`
  line `paid-up equity capital of the association;`
  line
  line `^3[(e)] the restriction on the right of a member to appoint another person as his proxy to attend and`
  line `vote at a meeting of the association;`
  line
  line `^4[(f)] the retirement at every annual general meeting of all directors or such number or proportion`
  line `of their total number as may be specified in the rules;]`
  line
  line `^3[(g)] such incidental, consequential and supplementary matters as may be necessary to give`
  line `effect to any of the matters specified in ^5[clauses (a) to (f).]`
  line
  line `(2) No rules of a recognised association made or amended in relation to any matter referred to in`
  line `^6[clauses (a) to (g)] of sub-section (1) shall have effect until they have been approved by the Central`
  line `Government and published by that Government in the Official Gazette and, in approving the rules so made or amended, the Central Government may make such modifications therein as it thinks fit, and on`
  line `such publication, the rules as approved by the Central Government shall be deemed to have been validly`
  line `made, notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956).`
  line
  line `(3) Where, before the commencement of the Forward Contracts (Regulation) Amendment Act, 1957`
  line `(3 of 1957), any rules have been made or amended in relation to any matter referred to in ^7[clauses (b) to`
  line `(e) and (g)] of sub-section (1), the rules so made or amended shall not be deemed to be invalid or ever to`
  line `have been invalid merely by reason of the fact that the rules so made or amended are repugnant to any of`
  line `the provisions of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956).]`
obj_root_law_sections_9_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 32 of 1957, s. 2, for section 9A (w.e.f. 17-9-1957)`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 17-9-1957).`
  line
  line `3. Clauses (a), (b), (c), (d) and (e) re-lettered as clauses (b), (c), (d), (e) and (g) Act by 62 of 1960, s. 9 (w.e.f. 28-12-1960).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by s. 9, ibid. (we.f. 28-12-1960).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 9, ibid., for "clauses (a), (b), (c) and (d)" (w.e.f. 28-12-1960).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by s. 9, ibid., for "clauses (a) to (e)@/"i@ (w.e.f. 28-12-1960).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 62 of 1960, s. 9, for "clauses (a) to (e)" (w.e.f. 281-12-1960).`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (4580)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 12
  title `Power of Central Government to direct rules to be made or to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 10, ibid., for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 28-12-1960).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287&sectionId=4580&sectionno=10&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever`
  line `the Central Government considers it expedient so to do, it may, by order in writing, direct any recognised`
  line `association to make any rules or to amend any rules made by the recognised association within such`
  line `period as it may specify in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) If any recognised association, against whom an order is issued by the Central Government under`
  line `sub-section (1), fails or neglects to comply with such order within the specified period, the Central`
  line `Government may make the rules or amend the rules made by the recognised association, as the case may`
  line `be, either in the form specified in the order or with such modification thereof as the Central Government`
  line `may think fit.`
  line
  line `^1[(3) Where, in pursuance of sub-section (2), any rules have been made or amended, the rules so made`
  line `or amended shall be published in the Gazette of India, and shall, thereupon, have effect notwithstanding`
  line `anything to the contrary contained in the Companies Act, 1956, or any other law for the time being in`
  line `force, as if they had been made or amended by the recognised association concerned.]`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (4581)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 13
  title `Power of recognised association to make bye-laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287&sectionId=4581&sectionno=11&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any recognised association may,`
  line `subject to the previous approval of the Central Government, make bye-laws for the regulation and control`
  line `of forward contracts.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such bye-laws may`
  line `provide for--`
  line
  line `(a) the opening and closing of markets and the regulation of the hours of trade;`
  line
  line `(b) a clearing house for the periodical settlement of contracts and differences thereunder, the`
  line `delivery of, and payment for, goods, the passing on of delivery orders and for the regulation and`
  line `maintenance of such clearing house;`
  line
  line `(c) the number and classes of contracts in respect of which settlements shall be made or`
  line `differences paid through the clearing house;`
  line
  line `(d) fixing, altering or postponing days for settlement;`
  line
  line `(e) determining and declaring market rates, including opening, closing, highest and lowest rates`
  line `for goods;`
  line
  line `(f) the terms, conditions and incidents of contracts including the prescription of margin`
  line `requirements, if any, and conditions relating thereto, and the forms of contracts in writing;`
  line
  line `(g) regulating the entering into, making, performance, rescission and termination of contracts,`
  line `including contracts between members or between a commission agent and his constituent, or between`
  line `a broker and his constituent, or between a member of the recognised association and a person who is`
  line `not a member, and the consequences of default or insolvency on the part of a seller or buyer or`
  line `intermediary, the consequences of a breach or omission by a seller or buyer and the responsibility of`
  line `commission agents and brokers who are not parties to such contracts;`
  line
  line `(h) the admission and prohibition of specified classes or types of goods or of dealings in goods by`
  line `a member of the recognised association;`
  line
  line `(i) the method and procedure for the settlement of claims or disputes including the settlement`
  line `thereof by arbitration;`
  line
  line `(j) the levy and recovery of fees, fines and penalties;`
  line
  line `(k) the regulation of the course of business between parties to contracts in any capacity;`
  line
  line `(l) the fixing of a scale of brokerage and other charges;`
  line
  line `(m) the making, comparing, settling and closing of bargains;`
  line
  line `(n) the regulation of fluctuations in rates and prices;`
  line
  line `(o) the emergencies in trade which may arise and the exercise of powers in such emergencies`
  line `including the power to fix maximum and minimum prices;`
  line
  line `(p) the regulation of dealings by members for their own account;`
  line
  line `(q) the limitations on the volume of trade done by any individual member;`
  line
  line `(r) the obligation of members to supply such information or explanation and to produce such`
  line `books relating to their business as the governing body may require.`
  line
  line `(3) The bye-laws made under this section may--`
  line
  line `(a) specify the bye-laws the contravention of any of which shall make a contract entered into`
  line `otherwise than in accordance with the bye-laws void under sub-section (2) of section 15;`
  line
  line `^1[(aa) specify the bye-laws the contravention of any of which shall make a forward contract`
  line `entered into otherwise than in accordance with bye-laws illegal under sub-section (3A) of section 15;]`
  line
  line `(b) provide that the contravention of any of the bye-laws shall--`
  line
  line `(i) render the member concerned liable to fine; or`
  line
  line `(ii) render the member concerned liable to expulsion or suspension from the recognised`
  line `association or to any other penalty of a like nature not involving the payment of money.`
  line
  line `(4) Any bye-laws made under this section shall be subject to such conditions in regard to previous`
  line `publication as may be prescribed, and when approved by the Central Government, shall be published in`
  line `the Gazette of India ^2***:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, in the interest of the trade or in the public interest, by`
  line `order in writing, dispense with the condition of previous publication, in any case`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 62 of 1960, s. 11 (w.e.f. 28-12-1960).`
  line
  line `2. The words "and also in the Official Gazette of the State in which the principal office of the recognised association is situate"`
  line `omitted by s. 12, ibid. (w.e.f. 28-12-1960).`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (4582)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 14
  title `Power of Central Government to make or amend bye-laws of recognised associations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287&sectionId=4582&sectionno=12&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `The Central Government may, either on a request in writing received by it in this behalf from the`
  line `governing body of a recognised association, or if in its opinion it is expedient so to do, make bye-laws for`
  line `all or any of the matters specified in section 11 or amend any bye-laws made by such association under`
  line `that section.`
  line
  line `(2) Where, in pursuance of this section, any bye-laws have been made or amended, the bye-laws so`
  line `made or amended shall be published in the Gazette of India ^1[and shall thereupon have effect].`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in this section, where the governing body of a recognised`
  line `association objects to any bye-laws made or amended under this section by the Central Government on its`
  line `own motion, it may, within six months of the publication thereof under sub-section (2), apply to the`
  line `Central Government for a revision thereof, and the Central Government may, after giving a reasonable`
  line `opportunity to the governing body of the association to be heard in the matter, revise the bye-laws so`
  line `made or amended, and where any bye-laws so made or amended are revised as a result of any action takenunder this sub-section the bye-laws so revised shall be published and shall become effective as provided`
  line `in sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(4) The making or the amendment or revision of any bye-laws under this section shall in all cases be`
  line `^2[subject to such conditions in regard to previous publication as may be prescribed.]`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, in the interest of the trade or in the public interest, by`
  line `order in writing, dispense with the condition of previous publication in any case.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 12, ibid., for "subject to the condition of previous publication" (w.e.f. 28-12-1960).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 62 of 1960, s. 12, for "subject to the condition of previous publication" (w.e.f. 28-12-1960)`
obj_root_law_sections_12_a:
  sectionId (4583)
  sectionNo 12A
  orderNo 15
  title `Application of amendment of bye-laws to existing forward contracts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 13, ibid. (w.e.f. 28-12-1960).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287&sectionId=4583&sectionno=12A&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287
obj_root_law_sections_12_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[12A. Application of amendment of bye-laws to existing forward contracts.--Any amendment of`
  line `a bye-law under section 11 other than an amendment made in pursuance of clause (a) or clause (aa) of`
  line `sub-section (3) of that section or under section 12 also apply to all forward contracts entered into before`
  line `the date of its approval by the Central Government or before the date of its publication in the Gazette of`
  line `India, as the case may be, and remaining to be performed on or after the said date.]`
obj_root_law_sections_12_b:
  sectionId (4584)
  sectionNo 12B
  orderNo 16
  title `Power of Commission to suspend member of recognised association or to prohibit him from trading.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 13, ibid. (w.e.f. 28-12-1960).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287&sectionId=4584&sectionno=12B&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287
obj_root_law_sections_12_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[12B. Power of Commission to suspend member of recognised association or to prohibit him`
  line `from trading.--(1) If, in the interest of trade or in the public interest, the Commission considers it`
  line `necessary to suspend a member from his membership of any recognised association or to prohibit such`
  line `members from entering into any forward contract for the sale or purchase in his own name or through`
  line `another member of a recognised association of any goods or class of goods, then, notwithstanding`
  line `anything contained in any law for the time being in force or in the rules or bye-laws of a recognised`
  line `association, the Commission may, after giving an opportunity of being heard, by order suspend his`
  line `membership of any association or prohibit him from entering into any such contract.`
  line
  line `(2) An order under sub-section (1) shall specify the period for which the suspension or prohibition is`
  line `to have effect and such period may be extended from time to time but so as not to exceed three years in`
  line `the aggregate.`
  line
  line `(3) No order made under sub-section (1) in respect of any member of a recognised association shall`
  line `affect the validity of anyforward contract entered into or made by, with or through such member on or`
  line `before the date of such order and remaining to be performed on or after the said date; but the Commission`
  line `may make such provision as it deems fit in such order or in any subsequent order for the closing out of`
  line `any such forward contract.]`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (4585)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 17
  title `Power of Central Government to supersede governing body of recognised association.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287&sectionId=4585&sectionno=13&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `Without prejudice to any other powers vested in the Central Government under this Act, where the`
  line `Central Government is of opinion that the governing body of any recognised association should be`
  line `superseded, then, notwithstanding anything contained in this Act or in any other law for the time being in`
  line `force, the Central Government may, after giving a reasonable opportunity to the governing body of the`
  line `recognised association concerned to show cause why it should not be superseded, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, declare the governing body of such association to be superseded for such period not`
  line `exceeding six months as may be specified in the notification, and may appoint any person or persons to`
  line `exercise and perform all the powers and duties of the governing body, and where more persons than one`
  line `are appointed may appoint one of such persons to be the chairman and another of such persons to be the`
  line vice-chairman.
  line
  line `(2) On the publication of a notification in the Official Gazette under sub-section (1), the following`
  line `consequences shall ensue, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the members of the governing body which has been superseded shall, as from the date of the`
  line `notification of supersession cease to hold office as such members;`
  line
  line `(b) the person or persons appointed under sub-section (1) may exercise and perform all the`
  line `powers and duties of the governing body which has been superseded;`
  line
  line `(c) all such property of the recognised association as the person or persons appointed under`
  line `sub-section (1) may, by order in writing, specify in this behalf as being necessary for the purpose of`
  line `enabling him or them to carry out the purposes of this Act, shall vest in such person or persons.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in any law or the rules or bye-laws of the`
  line `association whose governing body is superseded under sub-section (1), the person or persons appointed`
  line `under that sub-section shall hold office for such period as may be specified in the notification published`
  line `under that sub-section, and the Central Government may, from time to time, by like notification vary such`
  line period.
  line
  line `(4) On the determination of the period of office of any person or persons appointed under this section`
  line `the recognised association shall forthwith reconstitute a governing body in accordance with its rules:`
  line
  line `Provided that until a governing body is so reconstituted, the person or persons appointed under`
  line `sub-section (1) shall, notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), continue to exercise and`
  line `perform their powers and duties.`
  line
  line `(5) On the reconstitution of a governing body under sub-section (4), all the property of the recognised`
  line `association which had vested in, or was in the possession of, the person or persons appointed under`
  line `sub-section (1) shall vest or revest, as the case may be, in the governing body so reconstituted.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (4586)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 18
  title `Power to suspend business of recognised association.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287&sectionId=4586&sectionno=14&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `If in the interest of the trade or in the`
  line `public interest the Central Government considers it expedient so to do, it may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, direct a recognise association to suspend such of its business for such period not`
  line `exceeding seven days and subject to such conditions as may be specified in the notification, and may if, in`
  line `the opinion of the Central Government, the interest of the trade or the public interest to requires by like`
  line `notification extend the said period from time to time:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the period of suspension is likely to exceed one month, no notification extending`
  line `the suspension beyond such period shall be issued, unless the governing body of the recognised`
  line `association has been given an opportunity of being heard in the matter.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14_a:
  sectionId (4587)
  sectionNo 14A
  orderNo 19
  title `Certificate of registration to be obtained by all associations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 62 of 1960, s. 14 (w.e.f. 281-12-1960).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287&sectionId=4587&sectionno=14A&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287
obj_root_law_sections_14_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[14A. Certificate of registration to be obtained by all associations.--(1) No association concerned`
  line `with regulation and control of business relating to forward contracts shall, after the commencement of the`
  line `Forward Contracts (Regulation) Amendment Act, 1960 (62 of 1960) (hereinafter referred to as such`
  line `commencement) carry on such business except under, and in accordance with, the conditions of a`
  line `certificate of registration granted under this Act by the Commission.`
  line
  line `(2) Every association referred to in sub-section (1) which is in existence at such commencement,`
  line `before the expiry of six months from such commencement, and every association referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1) which is not in existence at such commencement, before commencing such business, shall`
  line `make an application for a certificate of registration to the Commission in such form and containing such`
  line `particulars as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Commission may in its discretion extend from time to time the period of six months`
  line `aforesaid up to one year in the aggregate.`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing in this section shall be deemed--`
  line
  line `(a) to prohibit an association in existence at such commencement from carrying on its business`
  line `until the disposal of the application made by it under sub-section (2); or`
  line
  line `(b) to require a recognised association in existence at such commencement to make an application`
  line `under sub-section (2); and every such association shall, as soon as may he after such commencement,`
  line `be granted free of cost by the Commission a certificate of registration.]`
obj_root_law_sections_14_b:
  sectionId (4588)
  sectionNo 14B
  orderNo 20
  title `Grant or refusal of certificate of registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 62 of 1960, s. 14 (w.e.f. 281-12-1960).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287&sectionId=4588&sectionno=14B&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287
obj_root_law_sections_14_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[14B. Grant or refusal of certificate of registration.--On receipt of an application under section`
  line `14A, the Commission, after making such inquiry as it considers necessary in this behalf, may by order in`
  line `writing grant a certificate of registration or refuse to grant it:`
  line
  line `Provided that before refusing to grant such certificate, the association shall be given an opportunity of`
  line `beng heard in the matter.]`
obj_root_law_sections_14_c:
  sectionId (4589)
  sectionNo 14C
  orderNo 21
  title `Application of sections 8 and 12B to registered associations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_c_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 62 of 1960, s. 14 (w.e.f. 281-12-1960).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287&sectionId=4589&sectionno=14C&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287
obj_root_law_sections_14_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[14C. Application of section 8 and 12B to registered association.--The provisions of sections 8 and`
  line `12B shall apply in relation to a registered association as they apply in relation to a recognised association`
  line `with the substitution of--`
  line
  line `(i) references to the registered association, for references to the recognised association; and`
  line
  line `(ii) the words "two years" for the words "three years" in sub-section (2) of section 12B.]`
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (4590)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 22
  title `Forward contracts in notified goods illegal or void in certain circumstances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 62 of 1960, s. 15 (w.e.f. 28-12-1960).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287&sectionId=4590&sectionno=15&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, declare this section to apply to such`
  line `goods or class of goods and in such areas as may be specified in the notification, and thereupon, subject to`
  line `the provisions contained in section 18, every forward contract for the sale or purchase of any goods`
  line `specified in the notification which is entered into in the area specified therein otherwise than between`
  line `members of a recognised association or through or with any such member shall be illegal.`
  line
  line `(2) Any forward contract in goods entered into in pursuance of sub-section (1) which is in`
  line `contravention of any of the bye-laws specified in this behalf under clause (a) of sub-section (3) of section`
  line `11 shall be void--`
  line
  line `(i) as respects the rights of any member of the recognised association who has entered into such`
  line `contract in contravention of any, such bye-law, and also`
  line
  line `(ii) as respects the rights of any other person who has knowingly participated in the transaction`
  line `entailing such contravention.`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing in sub-section (2) shall affect the right of any person other than a member of the`
  line `recognised association to enforce any such contract or to recover any sum under or in respect of such`
  line `contract:`
  line
  line `Provided that such person had no knowledge that such transaction was in contravention of any of the`
  line `bye-laws specified under clause (a) of sub-section (3) of section 11.`
  line
  line `^1[(3A) Any forward contract in goods entered into in pursuance of sub-section (1) which at the date of`
  line `the contract is in contravention of any of the bye-laws specified in this behalf under clause (aa) of`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 11 shall be illegal.]`
  line
  line `(4) No member of a recognised association shall, in respect of any goods specified in the notification`
  line `under sub-section (1), enter into any contract on his own account with any person other than a member of`
  line `the recognised association, unless he has secured the consent or authority of such person and discloses in`
  line `the note, memorandum or agreement of sale or purchase that he has bought or sold the goods, as the case`
  line `may be, on his own account:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the member has secured the consent or authority of such person otherwise than in`
  line `writing he shall secure a written confirmation by such person of such consent or authority within three`
  line `days from the date of such contract :`
  line
  line `Provided further that in respect of any outstanding contract entered into by a member with a person`
  line `other than a member of the recognised association, no consent or authority of such person shall be`
  line `necessary for closing out in accordance with the bye-laws the outstanding contract, if the member`
  line `discloses in the note, memorandum or agreement of sale or purchase in respect of such closing out that he`
  line `has bought or sold the goods, as the case may be, on his own account`
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (4591)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 23
  title `Consequences of notification under section 15.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 62 of 1960, s. 16, for "entered into before the date of the notification" (w.e.f. 28-12-1960).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287&sectionId=4591&sectionno=16&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `Where a notification has been issued under`
  line `section 15, then notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force or in anycustom, usage or practice of the trade or the terms of any contract or the bye-laws of any association`
  line `concerned relating to any contract,--`
  line
  line `(a) every forward contract for the sale or purchase of any goods specified in the notification,`
  line `^1[entered into on or before the date of the notification] and remaining to be performed after the said`
  line `date and which is not in conformity with the provisions of section 15, shall be deemed to be closed`
  line `out at such rate as the Central Government may fix in this behalf, and different rates may be fixed for`
  line `different classes of such contracts;`
  line
  line `(b) all differences arising out of any contract so deemed to be closed out shall be payable on the`
  line `basis of the rate fixed under clause (a) and the seller shall not be bound to give and the buyer shall not`
  line `be bound to take delivery of the goods.`
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (4592)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 24
  title `Power to prohibit forward contracts in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 62 of 1960, s. 16, for "entered into before the date of the notification" (w.e.f. 28-12-1960).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287&sectionId=4592&sectionno=17&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, declare that no person shall, save with the permission of the Central`
  line `Government, enter into any forward contract for the sale or purchase of any goods or class of goods`
  line `specified in the notification and to which the provisions of section 15 have not been made applicable,`
  line `except to the extent and in the manner, if any, as may be specified in the notification.`
  line
  line `(2) All forward contracts in contravention of the provisions of sub-section (1) entered into after the`
  line `date of publication of the notification thereunder shall be illegal.`
  line
  line `(3) Where a notification has been issued under sub-section (1), the provisions of Section 16 shall, in`
  line `the absence of anything to the contrary in the notification, apply to all forward contracts for the sale or`
  line `purchase of any goods specified in the notification ^1[entered into on or before the date of the notification]`
  line `and remaining to be performed after the said date as they apply to all forward contracts for the sale: or`
  line `purchase of any goods specified in the notification under section 15.`
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (4593)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 25
  title `Special provisions respecting certain kinds of forward contracts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287&sectionId=4593&sectionno=18&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) Nothing contained in`
  line `Chapter III or Chapter IV shall apply to non-transferable specific delivery contracts for the sale or`
  line `purchase of any goods:`
  line
  line `Provided that no person shall organise or assist in organising or be a member of any association in`
  line `any area to which the provisions of section 15 have been made applicable (other than a recognised`
  line `association) which provides facilities for the performance of any non-transferable specific delivery`
  line `contract by any party thereto without having to make or to receive actual delivery to or from the other`
  line `party to the contract or to or from any other party named in the contract.`
  line
  line `(2) Where in respect of any area the provisions of section 15 have been made applicable in relation to`
  line `forward contracts for the sale or purchase of any goods or class of goods, the Central Government may,`
  line `by a like notification, declare that in the said area or any part thereof as may be specified in the`
  line `notification all or any of the provisions of Chapter III or Chapter IV shall not apply to transferable`
  line `specific delivery contracts for the sale or purchase of the said goods or class of goods either generally, or`
  line `to any class of such contracts in particular.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), if the Central Government is of opinion`
  line `that in the interest of the trade or in the public interest it is expedient to regulate and control nontransferable`
  line `specific delivery contracts in any area, it may, by notification in the Official Gazette, declare`
  line `that all or any of the provisions of Chapters III and IV shall apply to such class or classes of nontransferable`
  line `specific delivery contracts in such area and in respect of such goods or class of goods as may`
  line `be specified in the notification, and may also specify the manner in which and the extent to which all or`
  line `any of the said provisions shall so apply.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (4594)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 26
  title `Prohibition of options in goods.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287&sectionId=4594&sectionno=19&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act or in any`
  line `other law for the time being in force, all options in goods entered into after the date on which this section`
  line `comes into force shall be illegal.`
  line
  line `(2) Any option in goods which has been entered into before the date on which this section comes into`
  line `force and which remains to be performed, whether wholly or in part, after the said date, shall, to that`
  line `extent, become void.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (4595)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 27
  title Penalties.
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 62 of 1960, s. 17, for section 20 (w.e.f. 28-12-1960).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287&sectionId=4595&sectionno=20&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `^1[20. Penalties.--Any person who--`
  line
  line `(a) (i) in any return, statement or other document required by or under this Act, makes a`
  line `statement which is false in any material particular, knowing it to be false, or willfully omits to make a`
  line `material statement; or`
  line
  line `(ii) without reasonable excuse (the burden of proving which shall be on him) fails to furnish any`
  line `return, statement or other document or any information or to answer any question or to comply with`
  line `any requisition made under this Act or any rules made thereunder; or`
  line
  line `(iii) enters into any forward contract during the period of suspension of business of a recognised`
  line `association in pursuance of a notification under section 14; or`
  line
  line `(b) is a member of any association, other than a recognised association, to which a certificate of`
  line `registration has not been granted under this Act; or`
  line
  line `(c) publishes or circulates information relating to the rate at which any forward contract has been`
  line `entered into in contravention of any of the bye-laws of a recognised association; or`
  line
  line `(d) organises, or assists in organising, or is a member of, any association in contravention of the`
  line `provisions contained in the proviso to sub-section (1) of section 18; or`
  line
  line `(e) enters into any forward contract or any option in goods in contravention of any of the`
  line `provisions contained in sub-section (1) or sub-section (3A) or sub-section (4) of section 15, section 17`
  line `or section 19,`
  line
  line `shall, on conviction, be punishable--`
  line
  line `(i) for a first offence, with imprisonment which may extend to one year, or with a fine of not less`
  line `than one thousand rupees, or with both;`
  line
  line `(ii) for a second or subsequent offence under clause (d), or under clause (e) [other than an offence`
  line `in respect of a contravention of the provisions of sub-section (4) of section 15], with imprisonment`
  line `which may extend to one year and also with fine: Provided that in the absence of special and adequate`
  line `reasons to the contrary to be mentioned in the judgment of the court, the imprisonment shall not be`
  line `less than one month and the fine shall not be less than one thousand rupees.]`
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (4596)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 28
  title `Penalty for owning or keeping place used for entering into forward contracts in goods.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287&sectionId=4596&sectionno=21&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `Any person who--`
  line
  line `(a) owns or keeps a place other man that of a recognised association, which is used for the`
  line `purpose of entering into or making or performing, whether wholly or in part, any forward contracts in`
  line `contravention of any of the provisions of this Act and knowingly permits such place to be used for`
  line `such purposes, or`
  line
  line `(b) without the permission of Central Government, organises, or assists in organising, or becomes`
  line `a member of, any association, other than a recognised association, for the purpose of assisting in`
  line `entering into or making or performing, whether wholly or in part, any forward contracts in`
  line `contravention of any of the provisions of this Act, or`
  line
  line `(c) manages, controls or assists in keeping any place other man that of a recognised association,`
  line `which is used for the purpose of entering into or making or performing, whether wholly or in part,`
  line `any forward contracts in contravention of any of the provisions of this Act or at which such forward contracts are recorded or adjusted, or rights or liabilities arising out of such forward contracts are`
  line `adjusted, regulated or enforced in any manner whatsoever, or`
  line
  line `(d) not being a member of a recognised association, willfully represents to, or induces, any person`
  line `to believe that he is a member of a recognised association or that forward contracts can be entered`
  line `into or made or performed, whether wholly or in part, under this Act through him, or`
  line
  line `(e) not being a member of a recognised association or his agent authorised as such under the rules`
  line `or by-laws of such association, canvasses, advertises or touts in any manner, either for himself or on`
  line `behalf of any other person, for any business connected with forward contracts in contravention of any`
  line `of the provisions of this Act, or`
  line
  line `(f) joins, gathers, or assists in gathering at any place, other than the place of business specified in`
  line `the bye-laws of a recognised association, any person or persons for making bids or offers or for`
  line `entering into or making or performing, whether wholly or in part, any forward contracts in`
  line `contravention of any of the provisions of this Act, or`
  line
  line `(g) makes, publishes or circulates any statement or information which is false and which he either`
  line `knows or believes to be false, affecting or tending to affect the course of business in forward contracts`
  line `in respect of goods to which the provisions of section 15 have been made applicable,`
  line ^1[or]
  line
  line `^1[(h) manipulates or attempts to manipulate prices in respect of forward contracts for the sale or`
  line `purchase of any goods specified in any notification under section 15, in any area specified in that`
  line notification,]
  line
  line `^2[shall, on conviction, be punishable--`
  line
  line `(i) for a first offence, with imprisonment which may extend to two years, or with fine of not less`
  line `than one thousand rupees, or with both;`
  line
  line `(ii) for a second or subsequent offence, with imprisonment which may extend to two years and`
  line `also with fine: provided that in the absence of special and adequate reasons to the contrary to be`
  line `entioned in the judgment of the court, the imprisonment shall not be less than one month and the fine`
  line `shall not be less than one thousand rupees.]`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 62 of 1960, s. 18 (w.e.f. 28-12-1960).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 18, ibid., for certain words (w.e.f. 28-12-1960).`
obj_root_law_sections_21_a:
  sectionId (4597)
  sectionNo 21A
  orderNo 29
  title `Power of court to order forfeiture of property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 19, ibid. (w.e.f. 28-12-1960)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287&sectionId=4597&sectionno=21A&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287
obj_root_law_sections_21_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[21A. Power of court to order forfeiture of property.--Any court trying an offence punishable`
  line `under section 20 or section 21 may, if it thinks fit and in addition to any sentence which it may impose for`
  line `such offence, direct that any money, goods or other property in respect of which the offence has been`
  line `committed, shall be forfeited to the Central Government.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, property in respect of which an offence has been`
  line `committed, shall include deposits in a bank where the said property is converted into such deposits.]`
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (4598)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 30
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287&sectionId=4598&sectionno=22&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an offence has been committed by a company, every person`
  line `who, at the time the offence was committed, was in charge of, and was responsible to the company for the`
  line `conduct of the business of the company, as well as the company, shall be deemed to be guilty of the`
  line `offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment provided in this Act, if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or`
  line `that he exercised all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where an offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent or`
  line `connivance of, or is attributable to any gross negligence on the part of, any director, manager, secretary or`
  line `other officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall also be deemed to be`
  line `guilty of that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means any body corporate and includes a firm or other association of individuals;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) "director", in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22_a:
  sectionId (4599)
  sectionNo 22A
  orderNo 31
  title `Power to search and seize books of account or other documents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 62 of 1960, s. 20 (w.e.f. 28-12-1960)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287&sectionId=4599&sectionno=22A&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287
obj_root_law_sections_22_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[22A. Power to search and seize books of account or other documents.--(1) Any presidency`
  line `magistrate or a magistrate of the first class may, by warrant, authorise any police officer not below the`
  line `rank of sub-inspector to enter upon and search any place where books of account or other documents`
  line `relating to forward contracts or options in goods entered into contravention of the provisions of this Act,`
  line `may be or may be reasonably suspected to be, and such police officer may seize any such book or`
  line `document, if in his opinion, it relates to any such forward contract or option in goods.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1898 (5 of 1898), shall, so far as may be, apply`
  line `to any search or seizure made under sub-section (1) as they apply to any search or seizure made under the`
  line `authority of a warrant issued under section 98 of the said Code.]`
obj_root_law_sections_22_b:
  sectionId (4600)
  sectionNo 22B
  orderNo 32
  title `Presumptions to be drawn in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 62 of 1960, s. 20 (w.e.f. 28-12-1960)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287&sectionId=4600&sectionno=22B&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287
obj_root_law_sections_22_b_content:
  string
  line `^122B. Presumptions to be drawn in certain cases.--(1) Where any books of account or other`
  line `documents are seized from any place and there are entries therein making reference to quantity,`
  line `quotations, rates, months of delivery, receipt or payment of differences or sale or purchase of goods or`
  line `option in goods, such books of account or other documents shall be admitted in evidence without`
  line `witnesses having to appear to prove the same; and such entries shall be prima facie evidence of the`
  line `matters, transactions and accounts purported to be therein recorded.`
  line
  line `(2) In any trial for an offence punishable under section 21, it shall be presumed, until the contrary is`
  line `proved, that the place in which the books of account or other documents referred to in sub-section (1)`
  line `were seized, was used, and that the persons found therein were present, for the purpose of committing the`
  line `said offence.]`
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (4601)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 33
  title `Certain offences to be cognizable.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 21, ibid., for certain words (w.e.f. 28-12-1960).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287&sectionId=4601&sectionno=23&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of`
  line `Criminal Procedure, 1898 (5 of 1898),`
  line `^1[the following offences shall be deemed to be cognizable within`
  line `the meaning of that Code, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) an offence falling under sub-clause (ii) of clause (a) of section 20 in so far as it relates to the`
  line `failure to comply with any requisition made under sub-section (3) of section 8;`
  line
  line `(b) an offence falling under clause (d) of section 20;`
  line
  line `(c) an offence falling under clause (e) of section 20 other than a contravention of the provisions of`
  line `sub-section (3A) or sub-section (4) of section 15;`
  line
  line `(d) an offence falling under section 21.]`
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (4602)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 34
  title `Jurisdiction to try offences under this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287&sectionId=4602&sectionno=24&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `No court inferior to that of a presidency magistrate`
  line `or a magistrate of the first class shall take cognizance of or try any offence punishable under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (4603)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 35
  title `Advisory committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287&sectionId=4603&sectionno=25&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `For the purpose of advising the Central Government in relation to any`
  line `matter concerning the operation of this Act, the Central Government may establish an advisory committee`
  line `consisting of such number of persons as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (4604)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 36
  title `Power to delegate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287&sectionId=4604&sectionno=26&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, direct`
  line `that any power exercisable by it under this Act may, in such circumstances and subject to such conditions,`
  line `if any, as may be specified, be exercised by such officer or authority, including any State Government or`
  line `officers or authorities thereof as may be specified in the direction.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (4605)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 37
  title `Power to exempt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287&sectionId=4605&sectionno=27&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `exempt, subject to such conditions and in such circumstances and in such areas as may be specified in the`
  line `notification, any contract or class of contracts from the operation of all or any of the provisions of this`
  line Act.
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27_a:
  sectionId (4606)
  sectionNo 27A
  orderNo 38
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith .`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by act 62 of 1960, s. 22 (w.e.f. 28-12-1960).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287&sectionId=4606&sectionno=27A&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287
obj_root_law_sections_27_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[27A. Protection of action taken in good faith.--(1) No suit or other legal proceeding shall lie in`
  line `any court against the Central Government or any member, officer or servant of the Commission for`
  line `anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done under this Act, or any rule or bye-law made`
  line thereunder.
  line
  line `(2) No suit or other legal proceeding shall lie in any court against the government body or any`
  line `member, office-bearer or servant of any recognised association or against any person appointed under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 13 for anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done with the`
  line `approval, or at the instance, of the Commission and in pursuance of this Act, or of any rule or bye-law`
  line `made thereunder.]`
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (4607)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 39
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287&sectionId=4607&sectionno=28&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules for the purpose of carrying into effect, the objects of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for--`
  line
  line `(a) the terms and conditions of service of members of the Commission;`
  line
  line `(b) the manner in which applications for recognition may be made under section 5 and the levy of`
  line `fees in respect thereof;`
  line
  line `(c) the manner in which any inquiry for the purpose of recognising any association may be made`
  line `and the form in which recognition shall be granted;`
  line
  line `^1[(cc) the manner in which applications for certificates of registration may be made under`
  line `section 14A and the levy of fees in respect of such applications;]`
  line
  line `(d) the particulars to be contained in the annual reports of recognised associations;`
  line
  line `(e) the manner in which the bye-laws to be made, amended or revised under this Act shall, before`
  line `being so made, amended or revised be published for criticism;`
  line
  line `(f) the constitution of the advisory committee established under section 25, the terms of office of`
  line `and the manner of filling vacancies among members of the committee; the interval within which`
  line `meetings of the advisory committee may be held and the procedure to be followed at such meetings;`
  line `and the matters which may be referred by the Central Government to the advisory committee for`
  line advice;
  line
  line `(g) any other matter which is to be or may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `^2[(3) Every rule made under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in`
  line `one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule thereafter have effect only in`
  line `such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.]`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by s. 23, ibid. (w.e.f. 28-12-1960).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 4 of 1986, s. 2 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 15-5-1986)`
obj_root_law_sections_28_a:
  sectionId (4608)
  sectionNo 28A
  orderNo 40
  title `Savings of recognised associations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 131 (w.e.f. 28-9-2015).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287&sectionId=4608&sectionno=28A&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287
obj_root_law_sections_28_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[28A. Savings of recognised associations.--(1) All recognised associations under the Forward`
  line `Contracts Regulation Act, shall be deemed to be recognised stock exchanges under the Securities`
  line `Contracts (Regulation) Act, 1956 (42 of 1956) (herein referred to as the Securities Contracts Act):`
  line
  line `Provided that such deemed recognised stock exchanges shall not carry out any activity other than the`
  line `activities of assisting, regulating or controlling the business of buying, selling or dealing in commodity`
  line `derivatives till the said deemed recognised stock exchanges are specifically permitted by the Securities`
  line `and Exchange Board of India:`
  line
  line `Provided further that a person buying or selling or otherwise dealing in commodity derivatives as a`
  line `commodity derivatives broker, or such other intermediary who may be associated with the commodity`
  line `derivatives market, immediately before the transfer and vesting of rights and assets to the Securities and`
  line `Exchange Board of India for which no registration certificate was necessary prior to such transfer, may`
  line `continue to do so for a period of three months from such transfer or, if he has made an application for`
  line `such registration within the said period of three months, till the disposal of such application.`
  line
  line `(2) The Securities and Exchange Board of India (herein referred to as the Security Board) may`
  line `provide such deemed exchanges, adequate time to comply with the Securities Contracts Act and any`
  line `regulations, rules, guidelines or like instruments made under the said Act.`
  line
  line `(3) The bye-laws, circulars, or any like instrument made by a recognised association under the`
  line `Forward Contracts Act shall continue to be applicable for a period of one year from the date on which that`
  line `Act is repealed, or till such time as notified by the Security Board, as if the Forward Contracts Act had not`
  line `been repealed, whichever is earlier.`
  line
  line `(4) All rules, directions, guidelines, instructions, circulars, or any like instruments, made by the`
  line `Commission or the Central Government applicable to recognised associations under the Forward`
  line `Contracts Act shall continue to remain in force for a period of one year from the date on which that Act is`
  line `repealed, or till such time as notified by the Security Board, whichever is earlier, as if the Forward`
  line `Contracts Act had not been repealed.`
  line
  line `(5) In addition to the powers under the Securities Contracts Regulation Act, the Security Board and`
  line `the Central Government shall exercise all powers of the Commission and the Central Government with`
  line `respect to recognised associations, respectively, on such deemed exchanges, for a period of one year as if`
  line `the Forward Contracts Act had not been repealed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (4609)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 41
  title `Repeals and savings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 46 of 1953, s. 3 (w.e.f. 23-12-1953)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287&sectionId=4609&sectionno=29&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `^1[29. Repeals and savings.--If immediately before the date on which this Act or any provision`
  line `contained therein is made applicable to any goods or classes of goods in any State, there is in force in that`
  line `State any law corresponding to this Act or, as the case may be, to any provision contained therein which`
  line `is applicable to those goods or classes of goods, that law shall stand repealed on the said date:`
  line
  line `Provided that the repeal shall not affect--`
  line
  line `(a) the previous operation of any law so repealed or anything duly done or suffered thereunder; or`
  line
  line `(b) any right, privilege, obligation or liability acquired, accrued or incurred under any law so`
  line `repealed; or`
  line
  line `(c) any penalty, forfeiture or punishment incurred in respect of any offence committed against`
  line `any law so repealed; or`
  line
  line `(d) any investigation, legal proceeding or remedy in respect of any such right, privilege,`
  line `obligation, liability, penalty, forfeiture or punishment as aforesaid;`
  line
  line `and any such investigation, legal proceeding or remedy may be instituted, continued or enforced: and any`
  line `such penalty, forfeiture or punishment may be imposed as if this Act had not been passed:`
  line
  line `Provided further that, subject to the preceding proviso, anything done or any action taken (including`
  line `any appointment made, notification or order issued, rule, regulation, form or bye-law framed, or`
  line `recognition granted) under any such law shall be deemed to have been done or taken under the`
  line `corresponding provision of this Act, and shall continue to be in force accordingly unless and until`
  line `superseded by anything done or any action taken under this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_29_a:
  sectionId (4610)
  sectionNo 29A
  orderNo 42
  title `Repeal and savings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_a_content
  footnotes `1. Sections 29A or 29B shall stand by ins. (date to be notified) by Act 20 of 2015, s. 132`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287&sectionId=4610&sectionno=29A&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287
obj_root_law_sections_29_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[29A. Repeal and savings.--(1) The Forward Contracts (Regulation) Act, 1952 (74 of 1952) is`
  line `hereby repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) On and from the date of repeal of Forward Contracts Act--`
  line
  line `(a) the rules and regulations framed by the Central Government and the Commission under the`
  line `Forward Contracts Act, shall stand repealed;`
  line
  line `(b) all authorities and entities established by the Central Government under the Forward`
  line `Contracts Act, including the Commission and the Advisory Council established under section 25 of`
  line `that Act, shall stand dissolved;`
  line
  line `(c) anything done or any action taken or purported to have been done or taken including any`
  line `inspection, order, penalty, proceeding or notice made, initiated or issued or any confirmation or`
  line `declaration made or any licence, permission, authorisation or exemption granted, modified or`
  line `revoked, or any document or instrument executed, or any direction given under the Act repealed in`
  line `sub-section (1), shall be continued or enforced by the Security Board, as if that Act had not been`
  line repealed;
  line
  line `(d) all offences committed, and existing proceedings with respect to offences which may have`
  line `been committed under the Forward Contracts Act, shall continue to be governed by the provisions of`
  line `that Act, as if that Act had not been repealed;`
  line
  line `(e) a fresh proceeding related to an offence under the Forward Contracts Act, may be initiated by`
  line `the Security Board under that Act within a period of three years from the date on which that Act is`
  line `repealed and be proceeded with as if that Act had not been repealed;`
  line
  line `(f) no court shall take cognizance of any offence under the Forward Contracts Act from the date`
  line `on which that Act is repealed, except as provided in clauses (d) and (e);`
  line
  line `(g) clauses (d), (e) and (f) shall not be held to or affect the general application of section 6 of the`
  line `General Clauses Act, 1897 (10 of 1897) with regard to the effect of repeal to matters not covered`
  line `under these sub-sections.]`
obj_root_law_sections_29_b:
  sectionId (4611)
  sectionNo 29B
  orderNo 43
  title `Transfer and vesting of undertaking of Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_b_content
  footnotes `1. Sections 29A or 29B shall stand by ins. (date to be notified) by Act 20 of 2015, s. 132.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287&sectionId=4611&sectionno=29B&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00011_195274_1517807328287
obj_root_law_sections_29_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[29B. Transfer and vesting of undertaking of Commission.--- (1) On the date on which the Forward`
  line `Contracts Act is repealed, the undertaking shall be transferred, and vest with the Securities and Exchange`
  line `Board of India.`
  line
  line `(2) If there is any existing proceeding or cause of action against the Commission in relation to the`
  line `undertaking on the date on which the Forward Contracts Act is repealed, such proceeding or cause of`
  line `action may be continued and enforced by or against the Security Board.`
  line
  line `(3) The concessions, privileges, benefits and exemptions including any benefits and exemptions with`
  line `regard to the payment of any tax, duty and cess granted to the Commission with respect to its undertaking`
  line `shall be transferred to the Security Board on the date on which the Forward Contracts Act is repealed.`
  line
  line `(4) Every employee holding any office (excluding members of the Commission) under the`
  line `Commission immediately before the date on which the Forward Contracts Act is repealed, will hold office`
  line `in the Central Government or the Security Board, as the Central Government may notify in the Official`
  line `Gazette, for the same tenure and on the same terms and conditions of service as such employee would`
  line `have held such office if the Commission had not been dissolved:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the Central Government notifies that an employee of the Commission shall`
  line `continue as an employee of the Central Government under the foregoing provision, the Central`
  line `Government may, at the request of the Security Board, depute such employee to the Security Board, for a`
  line `period not exceeding two years from the date on which the Forward Contracts Act is repealed.`
  line
  line `(5) Within six months from the date on which the Forward Contracts Act is repealed, an employee of`
  line `the Commission opting not to be an employee of the Central Government or the Security Board, as the`
  line `case may be, shall communicate such decision to the Central Government or Security Board, as`
  line applicable.
  line
  line `(6) Nothing contained in any other law in force shall entitle any employee to any compensation for`
  line `the loss of office due to the repeal of the Forward Contracts Act and the consequent dissolution of the`
  line `Commission, and no such claim shall be entertained by any court, tribunal or other authority.`
  line
  line `(7) The members of the Commission appointed by the Central Government under section 3 of the`
  line `Forward Contracts Act, shall cease to hold office from the date the Forward Contracts Act is repealed.`
  line
  line `(8) The members of the Commission shall not be entitled to any compensation for the loss of office`
  line `due to the repeal of the Forward Contracts Act and the consequent dissolution of the Commission or for`
  line `the premature termination of any contract of management entered into by such member with the`
  line `Commission, and no such claim shall be entertained by any court, tribunal or other authority.`
  line
  line `(9) The transfer and vesting of the undertaking shall not be liable to the payment of any stamp duty`
  line `under the Indian Stamp Act, 1899 (2 of 1899) or any applicable stamp duties under state laws.]`
